So, if I want to reduce the parameter count, I should focus on the convolution part. One common technique to reduce parameters is to use depth-wise separable convolutions. Instead of having a single 1x1 convolution, which might have a lot of parameters depending on 'cin' and 'cout', I can split it into two steps: first, apply a depth-wise convolution, which only looks at each channel individually, and then a pointwise convolution to mix the channels.

